uid":61589,"like":27,"dislike":2,"score":25,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-12-18T05:07:13.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pediatric_intensive_care_unit?wprov=sfti1\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FPediatric_intensive_care_unit%3Fwprov%3Dsfti1&d=IZf6lr%2BCsfQX4MnErcdNIQHuyxefasl%2FZxVLfhQSBMM%3D&h=db8cda5d\" target=\"_blank\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pediatric_intensive_care_unit?wprov=sfti1</a><br />\nCorrect staffing is the next vital component to a successful PICU. <span style=\"color: red;\">The nursing staff is highly experienced in providing care to the most critical patients. The nurse to patient ratio should remain low, meaning that the nurses should only be caring for 1-2 patients depending on the clinical status of the patients.</span> If the patient&rsquo;s clinical status is critical, then they will require more monitoring and interventions than a patient that is stable.[7]<br />\n<br />\nIn most cases, <span style=\"color: red;\">the nurses and physicians are caring for the same patients for a long period of time. </span>This allows the providers to build rapport with the patients, so that all of the patient&rsquo;s needs are fulfilled. <br />\n<br />\nPICU病人同醫護一比一係理想既國際慣例<br />\n小朋友/BB正常黎講生cancer既機會好細<br />\n如果生親既多數都係好棘手既case<br />\n加上醫生長期follow同一個病人既話係比較理想<br />\n<br />\n呀樓主咁多「專家」意見<br />\n不如你又講下邊個發達國家係唔跟呢種practice ?<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"44d135a8ae027f0d721fcd3ec4c1cc7ed72b310d","tid":945574,"uid":83097,"like":6,"dislike":2,"score":4,"quote":{"pid":"a422d2042cd8c965983a09d31a990b9146bef4e2","tid":945574,"uid":61589,"like":27,"dislike":2,"score":25,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-12-18T05:07:13.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pediatric_intensive_care_unit?wprov=sfti1\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FPediatric_intensive_care_unit%3Fwprov%3Dsfti1&d=IZf6lr%2BCsfQX4Mn